		<body>
			<div type="transcription">
				<div type="original" xml:lang="de">
					<pb facs="EHRI-DC-059_01.png" n="1"/>
					<p>Protokoll Nr. 7</p>
					<p><date when="1945-08-12">12. 8. 1945</date></p>
					<p>Protokoll</p>
					<p>aufgenommen mit <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-730" type="subject">Klosterschwester</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_stauber_herma">Stauber Herma</persName>, geb. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-729" type="subject">Stift</term>
						<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3070820/mesto.html">Teplá</placeName>, Nationalität deutsch.</p>
					<p><q>Ich erinnere mich an zwei <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">Transporte</term>: an einen im <date when="1945-03">März</date> und einen in <date when="1945-04">April</date> d. J. Über den <term
								ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">Märztransport</term> kann ich nur sehr wenig sagen. Die Menschen hatten mangelhafte <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">Kleidung</term>, erfrorene
							Gliedmaßen, keinerlei Gepäck und sagten, sie gingen nach <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/2951839/bavaria.html">Bayern</placeName>. Sie wurden von <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1438" type="subject">SS-Aufsehern</term> begleitet.
							Etwa am <date when="1945-04-24">24. April</date> kam ein <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">Transport</term> von <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">Frauen</term> und <term
								ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">Männern</term> ins <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-728" type="subject">Kloster</term> und verlangte Platz zum Übernachten und <term
								ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">Kartoffeln</term>. Die Menschen waren in furchtbaren Zustand. Sie wurden auf verschiedene <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">Scheunen</term>
							aufgeteilt und ich begann für sie zu <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">kochen</term>. Einige <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">Frauen</term> halfen mir dabei. Während der
							Unterhaltung erfuhr ich, dass sie am <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">Transport</term> aus <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/3066138/silesia.html">Schlesien</placeName> nach <placeName
								ref="https://www.geonames.org/2951839/bavaria.html">Bayern</placeName> sind. Die Behandlung war zweierlei: ein <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1438" type="subject">Aufseher</term> wartete bis spät in die Nacht, bis alles <term
								ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">Essen</term> gekocht war und ging erst <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">schlafen</term>, als alle Leute versorgt waren. Es war ein <term
								ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-274" type="subject">älterer</term> Herr, dessen Namen ich mir nicht gemerkt habe. Er gab an, nur wider seinen Willen die <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1438"
								type="subject">Aufseherarbeit</term> übernommen zu haben und sprach seine Absicht aus, den <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">Transport</term> demnächst zu verlassen. Die <term
								ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">Gewalttaten</term> verabscheute er und schien bei den <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">Häftlingen</term> sehr beliebt zu sein. Ein anderer im
							Gegenteil <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">schlug</term> und schimpfte sogar auf die <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">Frauen</term>. Ich fühlte mich verpflichtet, ihm einen
							Verweis zu geben, worauf er sich gegen mich wandte. Sonst wissen wir im <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-728" type="subject">Kloster</term> darüber nichts.</q></p>
					<p>Protokoll aufgenommen durch <persName ref="#ehri_dc_shek_zeev">W. Zeew Scheck</persName> in Anwesenheit von <persName ref="#ehri_dc_ternerova_dorit">Dorit Terner</persName> und dem <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-730" type="subject"
							>Provisor</term> des <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-728" type="subject">Klosters</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_feyl_georg">Georg Feyl</persName>.</p>
					<p>Namen der Zeugen und Geburtsdaten:</p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_dc_shek_zeev">William Zeev Scheck</persName>
						<date when="1920-05-13">13. 5. 1920</date></p>
					<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-730" type="subject">Schwester</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_stauber_herma">Herma Stauber</persName>
						<date when="1897-05-01">1. 5. 1897</date></p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_dc_feyl_georg">Georg Feyl</persName>, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-730" type="subject">Provisor</term>, <date when="1894-06-02">2. 6. 1894</date></p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_dc_ternerova_dorit">Ternerová Dorit</persName>
						<date when="1925-09-28">28. 9. 1925</date></p>
				</div>
				<div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
					<pb facs="EHRI-DC-059_01.png" n="1"/>
					<p>Protocol No. 7</p>
					<p><date when="1945-08-12">12. 8. 1945</date></p>
					<p>Protocol</p>
					<p>recorded with <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-730" type="subject">monastic sister</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_stauber_herma">Stauber Herma</persName>, b.<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-729" type="subject">Stift</term>
						<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3070820/mesto.html">Teplá</placeName>, nationality German.</p>
					<p><q>I remember two<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject"> </term><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">transports</term>: one in <date when="1945-03">March</date> and one in <date
								when="1945-04">April</date>. I can say very little about the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">March transport</term>. The people had inadequate <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836"
								type="subject">clothing</term>, frozen limbs, no luggage and said that they were going to <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/2951839/bavaria.html">Bavaria</placeName>. They were accompanied by <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216"
								type="subject">SS guards</term>. Around <date when="1945-04-24">April 24</date>, a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">transport</term> of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject"
								>women</term> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> arrived at the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-728" type="subject">monastery</term> and demanded accommodation for the night
							and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">potatoes</term>. The people were in terrible condition. They were split up into different <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">barns</term>
							and I started to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">cook</term> for them. Some <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> helped me. During the conversation I learned that
							they were on the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">transport</term> from <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/3066138/silesia.html">Silesia</placeName> to <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/2951839/bavaria.html"
								>Bavaria</placeName>. The treatment was twofold: a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1438" type="subject">guard</term> waited until late in the night until all the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832"
								type="subject">food</term> was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">cooked</term> and did not go to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">sleep</term> until all the people were
							taken care of. It was an <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-274" type="subject">older</term> gentleman whose name I did not remember. He stated that he had only accepted the task of <term
								ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1438" type="subject">overseer</term> against his will and expressed his intention to leave the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">transport</term> soon. He loathed
							the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">violence</term> and seemed to be very popular with the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">inmates</term>. Another on the contrary <term
								ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">struck</term> and scolded even the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term>. I felt obliged to give him a reprimand, and he turned against
							me. Otherwise, we know nothing about it in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-728" type="subject">monastery</term>.</q></p>
					<p>Protocol recorded by <persName ref="#ehri_dc_shek_zeev">W. Zeew Scheck</persName> in the presence of <persName ref="#ehri_dc_ternerova_dorit">Dorit Terner</persName> and the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-730" type="subject">Provisor</term> of
						the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-728" type="subject">monastery</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_feyl_georg">Georg Feyl</persName>.</p>
					<p>Names and Birthdates of Witnesses:</p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_dc_shek_zeev">William Zeev Scheck</persName>
						<date when="1920-05-13">13. 5. 1920</date></p>
					<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-730" type="subject">Sister</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_stauber_herma">Herma Stauber</persName>
						<date when="1897-05-01">1. 5. 1897</date></p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_dc_feyl_georg">Georg Feyl</persName>, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-730" type="subject">Provisor</term>, <date when="1894-06-02">2. 6. 1894</date></p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_dc_ternerova_dorit">Ternerová Dorit</persName>
						<date when="1925-09-28">28. 9. 1925</date></p>
				</div>
			</div>
